// ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
// AKP Consulting Platform — Firebase Storage Security Rules
//
// Deploy via:
//   firebase deploy --only storage
//
// Or in Firebase Console:
//   Storage > Rules > paste this content > Publish
//
// ── Admin role enforcement ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Storage rules cannot read Firestore, so admin roles are enforced via
// Firebase Auth custom claims. Set these with the Admin SDK:
//
//   import { scripts/src/set-admin-claims.ts } (see that file for usage)
//
// The claim structure expected by these rules:
//   { role: "super_admin" | "admin_staff" | "instructor" | "client" | "student" | "accounting_partner" }
//
// Until custom claims are set, restrict admin Storage writes by deploying
// these rules and using the Admin SDK script to grant claims to your admins.
// ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

rules_version = '2';

service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {

    // ─── Helper functions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    function isSignedIn() {
      return request.auth != null;
    }

    function isOwner(uid) {
      return isSignedIn() && request.auth.uid == uid;
    }

    function userRole() {
      return request.auth.token.get('role', '');
    }

    function isAdmin() {
      return isSignedIn() && userRole() in ['super_admin', 'admin_staff'];
    }

    function isInstructor() {
      return isSignedIn() && userRole() in ['super_admin', 'admin_staff', 'instructor'];
    }

    // File size guard — prevent abuse via oversized uploads
    function isUnderSizeLimit(limitMB) {
      return request.resource.size < limitMB * 1024 * 1024;
    }

    // Restrict uploads to expected MIME types for document resources
    function isDocumentFile() {
      return request.resource.contentType in [
        'application/pdf',
        'application/vnd.ms-excel',
        'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet',
        'application/msword',
        'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document'
      ];
    }

    function isImageFile() {
      return request.resource.contentType.matches('image/.*');
    }

    // ─── Library resource files ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    // library/files/{resourceId}/{filename}
    //   Read:  public (anyone can download resources)
    //   Write: admin only, max 100 MB per file, document formats only

    match /library/files/{resourceId}/{filename} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if isAdmin()
                   && isUnderSizeLimit(100)
                   && isDocumentFile();
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Library thumbnails ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // library/thumbnails/{resourceId}/{filename}
    //   Read:  public
    //   Write: admin only, max 5 MB, images only

    match /library/thumbnails/{resourceId}/{filename} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if isAdmin()
                   && isUnderSizeLimit(5)
                   && isImageFile();
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Client documents ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // clients/{userId}/documents/{filename}
    //   Read:  owning user or admin
    //   Write: owning user (max 50 MB, document formats), admin can also write

    match /clients/{userId}/documents/{filename} {
      allow read: if isOwner(userId) || isAdmin();
      allow write: if (isOwner(userId) && isUnderSizeLimit(50) && isDocumentFile())
                   || isAdmin();
      allow delete: if isOwner(userId) || isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Avatars ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // avatars/{userId}/{filename}
    //   Read:  public (avatars shown in UI to other users)
    //   Write: owning authenticated user only, max 5 MB, images only

    match /avatars/{userId}/{filename} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if isOwner(userId)
                   && isUnderSizeLimit(5)
                   && isImageFile();
      allow delete: if isOwner(userId) || isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Course resources ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // courses/{courseId}/resources/{filename}
    //   Read:  authenticated users (enrolled check is best done server-side)
    //   Write: instructors and above, max 500 MB

    match /courses/{courseId}/resources/{filename} {
      allow read: if isSignedIn();
      allow write: if isInstructor() && isUnderSizeLimit(500);
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    match /courses/{courseId}/thumbnails/{filename} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if isInstructor()
                   && isUnderSizeLimit(10)
                   && isImageFile();
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    match /courses/{courseId}/lessons/{lessonId}/{kind}/{filename} {
      allow read: if isSignedIn();
      allow write: if isInstructor() && isUnderSizeLimit(500);
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Article images ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // articles/{articleId}/{filename}
    //   Read:  public
    //   Write: admin only, max 10 MB, images only

    match /articles/{articleId}/{filename} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if isAdmin()
                   && isUnderSizeLimit(10)
                   && isImageFile();
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Booking attachments ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Visitors can attach supporting documents/images to a booking request.

    match /bookings/{bookingRef}/attachments/{filename} {
      allow read: if isAdmin();
      allow create: if isUnderSizeLimit(25)
                    && (isDocumentFile() || isImageFile());
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // ─── Deny all other paths ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Any path not explicitly matched above is denied.
    // This is implicit in Firebase Storage rules, but making it explicit
    // signals intent and guards against accidental path additions.

    match /{allPaths=**} {
      allow read, write: if false;
    }

  }
}
